howard.edu.sycs363.spring15.SimpleAddressBook

Class AddressBook

  • java.lang.Object
    • howard.edu.sycs363.spring15.SimpleAddressBook.AddressBook

  • public class AddressBook
extends java.lang.Object
    An AdressBook class object holds information about a particular instance of an address book. The address book maintains/manages a list of Person objects that constitute an address list. The main responsibilities of this class include adding a new Person object to the address list, changing “mutable” (all properties except first and last name) information on a Person object, and deleting person object(s) from the maintained list. It also sorts the maintained address list by last name, and by zip code. And lastly, it saves the contents of the address list to a database, and or prints to a console output.

    • Method Detail

      • editEntry

        public void editEntry(int oldHashCode,
                      Person updatedPerson)
        Edit an entry in the address list

        This method tends to disguise edits by replacement. When a match is found in the map (using the hash code) the existing mapped value is replaced by the updated person object that is passed as a parameter. If oldHashCode is not a key is the map, then the function will return gracefully immediately.

        Parameters:
        oldHashCode - the hash code of the soon-to-be edited person object in the list
        updatedPerson - the replacement person object with the latest edits

      • addNewEntry

        public void addNewEntry(Person person)
        Add a new person to the address list

        If the person's hash code already exists as a key in the address list map (in which case, it is a duplicate), then a simple "like-for-like" replacement will occur.

        Parameters:
        person - the new person to be added to the address list

      • getEntry

        public java.util.ArrayList<Person> getEntry(java.lang.String lastName)
        Gets the Person(s) with the specified last name

        Since lastName cannot be unique, getEntry returns a list of person objects with the specified last name. An empty list is returned if there is no match.

        Parameters:
        lastName - the matching last name of the person(s) in the list
        Returns:
        a list of persons that match the given last name
